{
  "number": 5563,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/5563",
  "title": "feat(useInstantSearchApi): warn when an unstable search client is detected",
  "body": "One of the most common mistakes customers make is to provide a new instance of the search client at each re-render, often by instantiating the client inside their component. While this can sometimes be wanted (e.g., to update an ephemeral API key), this is more frequently an oversight which causes InstantSearch to dispatch more search requests than necessary.\r\n\r\nThis change adds a dev warning that lets you know of an unstable search client. I'll also update the linked docs to add a note on client stability.\r\n\r\nIf we're happy to move forward with this change, I'll do it for Vue InstantSearch as well.",
